1019:				;
1020:				; Runs code very similar to the stage 1 serial bootloader (the one normally
1021:				; entered from the front panel). This allows the monitor to be downloaded again.
1022:				; This is a simple binary download, with all received characters being written to
1023:				; RAM starting at address zero. There is no form of checksum or other
1024:				; verification. Termination is by reset from the front panel. The only functional
1025:				; difference between this and the stage 1 bootloader is that this allows the use
1026:				; of either serial port.
1027:				; The next thing in the command buffer should be the terminator.
